print("Walsh, Steven - Mid Term Program")

print("")

print( "Planet Express Delivery Time Calculator")

print("")

#Input
planet = input("What is the name of the planet?")
parsecs = float(input("How many parsecs away?"))
packages = int(input("How many packages?"))
tons = float(input("How many tons does each package weigh?"))

print("")

#Error Messages
if parsecs < 1:
  print("Error:", planet, "must be one or more parsecs away.")
if packages <= 0:
  print("Error: The ship must carry at least one package.")
if tons <= 0:
  print("Error: The package weight", tons, "is too light.")
  
print("")
  
#Warning Message
if packages > 10:
  if packages%2 != 0:
    print("Warning: Adjusting package count to", packages + 1)
    packages += 1

#Trip Time Calculations
tripTime1 = tons * packages * parsecs + parsecs
finalTript = tripTime1 + parsecs
finalTript = float(finalTript)

#Cargo Weight Calculations
cargoWeight = packages * tons

#Float Conversions
tripTime1 = float(tripTime1)
parsecs = float(parsecs)

#Final Calculations
print("The total cargo weight is", cargoWeight, "ton(s)")
print("The trip to", planet, "will take", tripTime1, "minutes.")
print("The trip back to Earth will take", parsecs, "minutes.")
print("The total trip time is", finalTript, "minutes.")

#Robot Planet
if planet == "Robot Planet":
  print("Also, Bender is great")
